==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Indraught
<hw>In"draught`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An
opening from the sea into the land; an inlet.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Sir W. Raleigh.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A draught of air or flow of water setting
inward.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indrawn</ent>⟦br⟧
